<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="231" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,348]" pageId="2" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,221,244]" pageId="2" pageNumber="231">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martins" box="[315,599,221,244]" pageId="2" pageNumber="231" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (2014 b) Subfamilia Lamiinae, Hemilophini Thomson, 1868. Parte II. Cerambycidae Sul- Americanos (Coleoptera) Taxonomia. Curitiba, Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, 14, 3 - 296." type="journal article" year="2014" yearSuffix="b">
Martins &amp; Galileo (
<number box="[523,579,221,244]" pageId="2" pageNumber="231" value="2014.0">2014</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
lists four species of 
<emphasis box="[817,962,220,244]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="231">
<taxonomicName box="[817,958,220,244]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Chrysaperda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chrysaperda</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
two of them known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1239,1330,221,244]" name="Ecuador" pageId="2" pageNumber="231">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, one from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,240,256,279]" name="Ecuador" pageId="2" pageNumber="231">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[291,340,256,279]" name="Peru" pageId="2" pageNumber="231">Peru</collectingCountry>
and one from 
<collectingCountry box="[494,559,256,279]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="231">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Amazonas). 
<taxonomicName box="[709,818,256,279]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Chrysaperda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[709,818,256,279]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="231">C. mimica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[824,910,256,279]" pageId="2" pageNumber="231" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[824,910,256,279]" pageId="2" pageNumber="231">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from the four species by the unicolorous, reddish-brown elytra. In all the other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[814,952,289,313]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Chrysaperda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[814,952,289,313]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="231">Chrysaperda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the elytra are black or metallic blue, with a transverse yellow fascia at the apex.
</paragraph>
